From: Anderson Nogueira <anderson.nogueira@percona.com>
Subject: [PATCH] router: strip -flto flags to prevent mysys duplication in plugins

LTO merges the static mysys convenience library into the mysqlrouter
binary and plugin .so files, creating multiple copies of the fivp file
info vector pointer (mysys/my_file.cc, anonymous namespace, internal
linkage per object). The binary's my_init() initializes only the
binary's fivp, leaving libmysqlrouter.so.1's copy as NULL. During
bootstrap, mysql_real_connect in libmysqlrouter.so.1 calls
mysql_init_character_set -> my_open -> RegisterFilename, which
dereferences the library's NULL fivp, causing SIGSEGV.

This follows the existing pattern in router/CMakeLists.txt (lines 37-38)
which strips -fuse-ld=gold for certain Clang versions.

Affects: Percona Server 8.0.43-34 through at least 8.0.45-36.
Ref: PS-10592, PKG-870, Forum #39242
---
 router/CMakeLists.txt | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/router/CMakeLists.txt b/router/CMakeLists.txt
index 0431cf37..d3b85a7a 100644
--- a/router/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/router/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -38,6 +38,16 @@ IF(USE_LD_LLD AND CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER_ID MATCHES "Clang" AND
   STRING(REPLACE "-fuse-ld=gold" "" CMAKE_CXX_LINK_FLAGS "${CMAKE_CXX_LINK_FLAGS}")
 ENDIF()

+# LTO merges static mysys into the binary and plugin .so files, creating
+# duplicate fivp copies. The binary's my_init() only initializes its own
+# copy, leaving libmysqlrouter.so.1's fivp NULL. Strip -flto from Router.
+IF(WITH_LTO)
+  STRING(REGEX REPLACE "-flto[^ ]*" "" CMAKE_C_FLAGS "${CMAKE_C_FLAGS}")
+  STRING(REGEX REPLACE "-flto[^ ]*" "" CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS "${CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS}")
+  STRING(REGEX REPLACE "-flto[^ ]*" "" CMAKE_CXX_LINK_FLAGS "${CMAKE_CXX_LINK_FLAGS}")
+  STRING(REGEX REPLACE "-flto[^ ]*" "" CMAKE_SHARED_LINKER_FLAGS "${CMAKE_SHARED_LINKER_FLAGS}")
+ENDIF()
+
 INCLUDE(cmake/version.cmake)
 SET(CMAKE_MODULE_PATH
   ${CMAKE_MODULE_PATH}
